member.name: M:StrictEmit.ILGeneratorExtensions.EmitCallIndirect(System.Reflection.Emit.ILGenerator,System.Reflection.CallingConventions,System.Type,System.Type[])
member.summary:
Puts a Calli instruction onto the Microsoft intermediate language (MSIL) stream, specifying a managed calling convention for the indirect call.
This method will use the unmanaged calling convention overload if available, and if not, fall back to the managed calling convention overload. This is done for backwards compatibility with Mono and the .NET Framework, which implement this overload. .NET Core does not implement it before version 2.1, and this method may therefore produce unexpected results on versions 2.0 and prior. In particular, it will default to the __fastcall unmanaged calling convention. As calling conventions are ignored on non-x86 platforms, this is usually not an issue.
member.param:
The generator where the IL is to be emitted.
[NotNull]
The managed calling conventions of the function pointer on the stack.

The return type of the managed function pointer. Defaults to void.
[CanBeNull]

The parameter types of the managed function pointer.
[NotNull]

member.summary:

In particular, it will default to the __fastcall unmanaged calling convention. As calling conventions are ignored on non-x86 platforms, this is usually not an issue.
member.param:
